    slug: 'writing-implementation-plans',
    name: 'Writing Implementation Plans',
    description:
      'Create bite-sized task plans with exact file paths, complete code, commands, verification steps. Make implementation obvious.',
    content:
      '# Writing Implementation Plans\n\n## Core Principle\n\nA good plan makes implementation obvious. If someone has to guess, the plan is incomplete.\n\nWrite comprehensive plans assuming the implementer has zero context. Document everything: which files to touch, complete code, testing commands, how to verify.\n\n## Bite-Sized Task Granularity\n\n**Each task = 2-5 minutes of focused work.**\n\nEvery step is one action:\n- "Write the failing test" — step\n- "Run it to make sure it fails" — step\n- "Implement the minimal code to make the test pass" — step\n- "Run the tests and make sure they pass" — step\n- "Commit" — step\n\n## Plan Document Structure\n\n### Header (Required)\n\n```markdown\n# [Feature Name] Implementation Plan\n\n**Goal:** [One sentence describing what this builds]\n\n**Architecture:** [2-3 sentences about approach]\n\n**Tech Stack:** [Key technologies/libraries]\n```\n\n### Task Structure\n\nEach task:\n\n````markdown\n### Task N: [Descriptive Name]\n\n**Objective:** What this task accomplishes (one sentence)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `exact/path/to/new_file.ts`\n- Modify: `exact/path/to/existing.ts:45-67` (line numbers if known)\n- Test: `tests/path/to/test_file.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write failing test**\n\n```typescript\ntest("specific behavior", () => {\n  const result = myFunction(input);\n  expect(result).toBe(expected);\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify failure**\n\nRun: `npm test -- specific.test.ts`\nExpected: FAIL — "myFunction is not defined"\n\n**Step 3: Write minimal implementation**\n\n```typescript\nfunction myFunction(input) {\n  return expected;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run test to verify pass**\n\nRun: `npm test -- specific.test.ts`\nExpected: PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/specific.test.ts src/file.ts\ngit commit -m "feat: add specific feature"\n```\n````\n\n## Key Principles\n\n**DRY (Don\'t Repeat Yourself):** Extract validation functions, use everywhere. Don\'t copy-paste.\n\n**YAGNI (You Aren\'t Gonna Need It):** Implement only what\'s needed now, not "flexibility" for future requirements.\n\n**TDD (Test-Driven Development):** Every task that produces code includes full TDD cycle: failing test → minimal code → passing test.\n\n**Frequent Commits:** Commit after every task.\n\n## Common Mistakes\n\n| Mistake | Bad | Good |\n|---------|-----|------|\n| Vague tasks | "Add authentication" | "Create User model with email and password_hash fields" |\n| Incomplete code | "Add validation function" (then blank) | Complete function code |\n| Missing verification | "Step 3: Test it works" | "Step 3: Run `npm test`, expected: 3 passed" |\n| Missing file paths | "Create the model file" | "Create: `src/models/user.ts`" |\n\n## Remember\n\n```\nBite-sized tasks (2-5 min each)\nExact file paths\nComplete code (copy-pasteable)\nExact commands with expected output\nVerification steps\nDRY, YAGNI, TDD\nFrequent commits\n```',
