    content:
      "# Feature Investigation & Research\n\n## Core Principle\n\nBefore building, understand what already exists. Find patterns, reuse them. Prevents architectural surprises and reinvention.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Before writing implementation plans\n- When starting a major feature\n- When working in an unfamiliar codebase\n- When choosing between multiple architectural approaches\n\n## Investigation Checklist\n\n### 1. Explore Project Structure\n\n- [ ] What's the overall architecture? (MVC, modular, service-oriented?)\n- [ ] How are files organized? (src/, features/, lib/)\n- [ ] What frameworks/libraries are in use?\n- [ ] What's the test structure? (unit/integration/e2e)\n- [ ] Are there existing similar features?\n\n### 2. Find Similar Patterns\n\nBefore designing, look for existing patterns:\n\n- [ ] How are other models/entities structured?\n- [ ] How are other endpoints/handlers implemented?\n- [ ] What testing patterns are used?\n- [ ] How is state managed?\n- [ ] What conventions are followed?\n\n### 3. Identify Files to Touch\n\n- [ ] Which files will need changes?\n- [ ] Which files should NOT be touched?\n- [ ] Are there interface files to understand?\n- [ ] What config files might need updates?\n\n### 4. Check Dependencies\n\n- [ ] What libraries already exist for this type of work?\n- [ ] Are there utilities that should be reused?\n- [ ] What's available vs what needs building?\n- [ ] Any platform/version constraints?\n\n### 5. Understand Existing Tests\n\n- [ ] Where are tests located?\n- [ ] What testing patterns are used?\n- [ ] How are mocks/fixtures set up?\n- [ ] What's the test execution command?\n\n## Output\n\nDocument findings in a `RESEARCH.md` file:\n\n```markdown\n# [Feature Name] Research\n\n## Architecture Overview\n[How the feature fits into the system]\n\n## Similar Existing Features\n[Patterns to reuse]\n\n## Files That Will Change\n[List with line numbers if known]\n\n## Dependencies & Utilities\n[What's available to use]\n\n## Test Patterns\n[How tests are structured in this project]\n\n## Constraints & Considerations\n[Version requirements, architectural rules, etc.]\n\n## Unknowns That Need Spiking\n[Things research can't answer — need experiments]\n```\n\n## Integration with Planning\n\nAfter investigation, use findings to inform your implementation plan:\n- Reuse patterns found\n- Touch the right files\n- Use existing utilities\n- Follow established testing conventions\n- Document any architectural decisions",
