    description:
      'Execute plans via fresh subagents per task with systematic two-stage review. Fresh context + early issue detection.',
    content:
      '# Subagent-Driven Execution\n\n## Core Principle\n\nFresh subagent per task + two-stage review (spec then quality) = high quality, fast iteration.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- You have an implementation plan\n- Tasks are mostly independent\n- Quality and spec compliance are important\n- You want automated review between tasks\n\n## The Process\n\n### 1. Read and Parse Plan\n\nRead the plan file completely. Extract ALL tasks upfront with their full text and context. Create a todo list.\n\n**Key:** Read the plan ONCE. Extract everything. Don\'t make subagents read the plan file — provide full task text in context.\n\n### 2. Per-Task Workflow\n\nFor EACH task in the plan:\n\n#### Step 1: Dispatch Implementer\n\nDelegate task with complete context:\n- Full task spec from plan\n- TDD instructions (RED → GREEN → REFACTOR)\n- Project context (structure, conventions, test commands)\n- Clear success criteria\n\n#### Step 2: Dispatch Spec Compliance Reviewer\n\nAfter implementer completes, verify against original spec:\n- All requirements from spec implemented?\n- File paths match spec?\n- Function signatures match spec?\n- Behavior matches expected?\n- Nothing extra added?\n\n**If spec issues found:** Implementer fixes, re-review. Continue only when PASS.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Code Quality Reviewer\n\nAfter spec compliance passes:\n- Follows project conventions and style?\n- Proper error handling?\n- Clear names?\n- Adequate test coverage?\n- No obvious bugs or security issues?\n\n**If quality issues found:** Implementer fixes, re-review. Continue only when APPROVED.\n\n#### Step 4: Mark Complete\n\nRecord task completion. Move to next task.\n\n### 3. Final Review\n\nAfter ALL tasks complete:\n\n- Do all components work together?\n- Any inconsistencies between tasks?\n- All tests passing?\n- Ready for merge?\n\n### 4. Verify and Commit\n\nRun full test suite. Review all changes. Final commit if needed.\n\n## Task Granularity\n\n**Each task = 2-5 minutes of focused work.**\n\n**Too big:** "Implement user authentication system"\n**Right size:** \n- "Create User model with email and password fields"\n- "Add password hashing function"\n- "Create login endpoint"\n- "Add JWT token generation"\n\n## Red Flags — Never Do These\n\n- Start implementation without a plan\n- Skip reviews (spec compliance OR code quality)\n- Proceed with unfixed critical/important issues\n- Dispatch multiple subagents on tasks that touch same files\n- Make subagents read plan file (provide full text in context)\n- Skip scene-setting context\n- Ignore subagent questions\n- Accept "close enough" on spec compliance\n- Skip review loops (found issues → fix → review again)\n- Let implementer self-review replace actual review\n- **Start quality review before spec compliance is PASS**\n- Move to next task while either review has open issues\n\n## When Issues Arise\n\n**If Subagent Asks Questions:** Answer clearly and completely. Don\'t rush into implementation.\n\n**If Reviewer Finds Issues:** Implementer subagent fixes them. Reviewer reviews again. Repeat until approved. Don\'t skip re-review.\n\n**If Subagent Fails Task:** Dispatch a new fix subagent with specific instructions about what went wrong. Don\'t manually fix in controller (context pollution).\n\n## Remember\n\n```\nFresh subagent per task\nTwo-stage review every time\nSpec compliance FIRST\nCode quality SECOND\nNever skip reviews\nCatch issues early\n```\n\n**Quality is not an accident. It\'s the result of systematic process.**',
